# Click hit-testing -- exercises the Click verb: resolves a box id against
# the render's BoxMap, failing (and naming the tape line) if the id is
# absent or its box is empty/zero-area. Source is the same sample.ctml the
# core DSL example (sample_test.ctml) renders, so the ids match its own
# Expect Box lines: banner (the <h1 id="banner">) and list (the
# <ul id="list">).
#
# Click is hit-testing only -- it proves a target CAN be hit, not that a
# click was dispatched anywhere. See doc.go's Click section for why driving
# an actual click (or a key) waits on a `hooks` prop this package does not
# have yet.

Source sample.ctml
Set Width 40

Data session.title "Welcome"
Data version "1.0"
Rows items 3

Click banner
Click list
